(5) One member of the Senate, appointed by the
281 President Pro Tempore of the Senate.
282 (6) One member of the House of Representatives,
283 appointed by the Speaker of the House of Representatives.
284 (7) One member of the Senate, appointed by the Minority
285 Leader of the Senate.
286 (8) One member of the House of Representatives,
287 appointed by the Minority Leader of the House of
288 Representatives.
289 (d) The committee shall meet at the call of the chair
290 or any two members, provided that the committee shall meet at
291 least once every six months. A majority of the members of the
292 committee shall constitute a quorum for the transaction of
293 business at meetings. Members of the committee shall be
294 entitled to their regular legislative compensation, per diem,
295 and travel expenses each day they attend a meeting of the
296 commission in accordance with Section 49 of the Constitution
297 of Alabama of 2022. These payments shall be paid out of any
298 funds appropriated for the use of the Legislature by means of
299 warrants drawn by the Comptroller on the State Treasury.
300 (e) Members of the committee may participate in a
301 meeting of the committee by means of telephone conference,
302 video conference, or similar communications equipment by means
303 of which all persons participating in the meeting may hear
304 each other at the same time. Participation by such means shall
305 constitute presence in person at a meeting for all purposes.
306 Section 2. (a) Chapter 2A of Title 29, Code of Alabama
307 1975, related to the Alabama Commission on the Evaluation of
308 Services, is repealed.
Page 11

Services, is repealed.
309 (b) Any reference in any law to the Alabama Commission
310 on the Evaluation of Services under Chapter 2A of Title 29,
311 Code of Alabama 1975, shall be deemed a reference to the
312 Alabama Commission on the Evaluation of Services created by
313 Section 1.
314 (c) The Alabama Commission on the Evaluation of
315 Services created by Section 1 shall be deemed a successor to
316 the Alabama Commission on the Evaluation of Services under
317 Chapter 2A of Title 29, Code of Alabama 1975 for all
318 contracts, agreements, and memorandums of understanding.
319 (d) On October 1, 2026, all papers, books, materials,
320 furnishings, funds, personnel, and property of the Alabama
